00:15:15,460 --> 00:15:18,600
- No, you should see what
the girls are wearing now,

265
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:20,280
it's not like in our day.

266
00:15:20,280 --> 00:15:22,150
- I didn't have a day.

267
00:15:22,150 --> 00:15:24,300
In (speaks in foreign
language) by the time

268
00:15:24,300 --> 00:15:25,400
I looked up from the pigs,

269
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:27,600
and the chickens, and the washing,

270
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:29,609
your momma's day came and went (whooshes).

271
00:15:29,609 --> 00:15:31,070
(Inez speaks in foreign language)

272
00:15:31,070 --> 00:15:33,170
My daughter's gonna have something better.

273
00:15:34,444 --> 00:15:38,190
- (speaks in foreign
language) made me such a gown.

274
00:15:38,190 --> 00:15:40,560
And I wore high heels for the first time.

275
00:15:40,560 --> 00:15:42,666
I'm almost walked off
the inside of my skirt.

276
00:15:42,666 --> 00:15:43,544
(group laughing)

277
00:15:43,544 --> 00:15:44,833
Yeah, but I looked good.

278
00:15:46,760 --> 00:15:50,170
- Did Momma tell you I
have to go with Octavio?

279
00:15:50,170 --> 00:15:52,800
- You should of seen the
cousin I had to go with.

280
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:55,265
Next to him Octavio looks
like Julio Iglesias.

281
00:15:55,265 --> 00:15:57,250
(group laughing)

282
00:15:57,250 --> 00:15:59,400
But cousins are safe, you know,

283
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,963
it's like they're spies for the father.

284
00:16:03,007 --> 00:16:04,130
- Mama.

285
00:16:04,130 --> 00:16:05,340
- Mija, after you turn 15

286
00:16:05,340 --> 00:16:07,380
you can make some of your own decisions.

287
00:16:07,380 --> 00:16:09,593
- Yeah, but until then it's Octavio.

288
00:16:10,912 --> 00:16:11,745
Ooh.

289
00:16:13,370 --> 00:16:16,393
- The quinceanera party
is only a celebration.

290
00:16:17,380 --> 00:16:20,560
Your true passage into
womanhood must be earned.

291
00:16:20,560 --> 00:16:22,920
Now how do you earn that passage?

292
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:25,300
Through service to others.

293
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:27,270
And you are all very fortunate

294
00:16:27,270 --> 00:16:30,870
because that opportunity exists right now.

295
00:16:30,870 --> 00:16:35,426
This is special time, historic time,

296
00:16:35,426 --> 00:16:37,276
(speaks in foreign language) amnesty.

297
00:16:38,460 --> 00:16:40,070
As our religion says-
- Tonight.

298
00:16:40,070 --> 00:16:41,163
- Forgiveness.

299
00:16:42,630 --> 00:16:44,370
Our church has set up an office

300
00:16:44,370 --> 00:16:46,770
to help people to fill
out amnesty applications.

301
00:16:46,770 --> 00:16:48,253
We need volunteers.

302
00:16:49,130 --> 00:16:49,963
Girls.

303
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:55,890
Marta, will you be of service?

304
00:16:55,890 --> 00:16:57,713
Will you be part of this forgiveness?

305
00:17:00,433 --> 00:17:02,142
(group chattering)

306
00:17:02,142 --> 00:17:04,132
(phone ringing)

307
00:17:04,132 --> 00:17:05,507
- Hundreds of thousands of immigrants

308
00:17:05,507 --> 00:17:07,290
live in this country illegally.

309
00:17:07,290 --> 00:17:09,620
The amnesty program started last year.

310
00:17:09,620 --> 00:17:11,370
It's their chance to come forward

311
00:17:11,370 --> 00:17:13,140
and be pardoned without punishment

312
00:17:13,140 --> 00:17:15,940
for having lived outside
the law until now.

313
00:17:15,940 --> 00:17:19,050
In time those who's qualify
will become residents

314
00:17:19,050 --> 00:17:21,800
and eventually United States citizens.

315
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:23,150
For the hours that you are here,

316
00:17:23,150 --> 00:17:25,650
you are be trusted with people's lives.

317
00:17:25,650 --> 00:17:27,320
Misplace an application form

318
00:17:27,320 --> 00:17:29,060
or forget to attach a money order

319
00:17:29,060 --> 00:17:31,570
and that person is as good as gone.

320
00:17:31,570 --> 00:17:34,980
Now application form here, medical exam,

321
00:17:34,980 --> 00:17:36,880
receipts, and verification.

322
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:38,270
Photo here.

323
00:17:38,270 --> 00:17:41,160
We have exactly four weeks left, 28 days.

324
00:17:41,160 --> 00:17:42,620
Every hour counts.

325
00:17:42,620 --> 00:17:43,847
Any questions?

326
00:17:44,789 --> 00:17:48,193
(phone ringing)

327
00:17:48,193 --> 00:17:49,610
Marta, the phone.

328
00:17:53,530 --> 00:17:54,363
- Hello.

329
00:17:58,640 --> 00:18:01,770
- They let children handle these matters.

330
00:18:01,770 --> 00:18:03,140
- Papi, we're not children.

331
00:18:03,140 --> 00:18:05,280
And besides these people need our help.

332
00:18:05,280 --> 00:18:06,400
- Yeah, but some of these people

333
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:07,360
have been waiting a long time

334
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:10,033
for a chance like this, too long.

335
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:13,240
You remember how it was,

336
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:15,890
if you didn't like it
here you could go back.

337
00:18:15,890 --> 00:18:16,940
- Are you through?

338
00:18:16,940 --> 00:18:18,853
- It's not a simple decision either.

339
00:18:19,857 --> 00:18:23,140
In Mexico things are easier.

340
00:18:23,140 --> 00:18:25,240
The life is not so fast.

341
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:27,567
- Oh, Samuel, you just
remember it that way.

342
00:18:27,567 --> 00:18:31,360
- No, the air is warm,
the people are warm,

343
00:18:31,360 --> 00:18:36,000
the sky is blue, the earth is rich.

344
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:37,750
Now in America a man can always improve,

345
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:39,100
yes, he can move up,

346
00:18:39,100 --> 00:18:42,977
but in Mexico a man can take time

347
00:18:42,977 --> 00:18:46,670
for his friends, for his family.

348
00:18:46,670 --> 00:18:48,540
- Papi, please can I be excused

349
00:18:48,540 --> 00:18:51,290
I have to meet my
girlfriends at the carnival.

350
00:18:51,290 --> 00:18:53,340
- Aren't you gonna help your mother?

351
00:18:53,340 --> 00:18:54,283
- Mommy, please.

352
00:18:55,350 --> 00:18:56,183
- Go.

353
00:19:00,380 --> 00:19:04,435
- Papi, me too, I have
some homework to do.

354
00:19:04,435 --> 00:19:07,660
- Homework, you're only
in the first grade.

355
00:19:07,660 --> 00:19:09,693
- Well, sorta like coloring.

356
00:19:10,845 --> 00:19:13,012
(Inez laughing)

357
00:19:13,012 --> 00:19:13,912
- Get out of here.

358
00:19:18,930 --> 00:19:20,714
Guess it's just you and me, buddy.

359
00:19:20,714 --> 00:19:21,633
- Yeah.

360
00:19:21,633 --> 00:19:24,423
Pop, tell me about the horses in Mexico.

361
00:19:25,860 --> 00:19:27,440
- I don't remember about any horses.

362
00:19:27,440 --> 00:19:30,740
- Yeah, you know the
one that threw you off.

363
00:19:30,740 --> 00:19:31,693
- Me?
- Yeah.

364
00:19:33,190 --> 00:19:34,023
- Never.

365
00:19:35,760 --> 00:19:38,360
That (speaks in foreign
language) was six feet tall.

366
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:41,983
I could see in her eyes
she would not be broken.

367
00:19:43,150 --> 00:19:45,810
I rode her for three and half hours, mijo.

368
00:19:45,810 --> 00:19:47,350
We fell in love.

369
00:19:47,350 --> 00:19:48,550
(lively music)

370
00:19:48,550 --> 00:19:51,467
(group chattering)

371
00:20:00,150 --> 00:20:01,810
- I couldn't believe it.

372
00:20:01,810 --> 00:20:04,250
I walked in and he was kissing her,

373
00:20:04,250 --> 00:20:06,380
I mean really kissing her.

374
00:20:06,380 --> 00:20:08,820
Their lips were together like Krazy Glue.

375
00:20:08,820 --> 00:20:11,090
You wonder how they could even breathe.

376
00:20:11,090 --> 00:20:14,060
- They can't, when people
kiss they can suffocate.

377
00:20:14,060 --> 00:20:15,310
- Then what happened?

378
00:20:15,310 --> 00:20:16,230
- The commercial came on

379
00:20:16,230 --> 00:20:17,604
and I had to help my mom fix dinner.

380
00:20:17,604 --> 00:20:18,437
(group groaning)

381
00:20:18,437 --> 00:20:19,270
- Jackie.

382
00:20:19,270 --> 00:20:21,020
- Well, I won't be home to watch tomorrow

383
00:20:21,020 --> 00:20:23,673
'cause I'm going on a
date with Billy Burton.

384
00:20:24,620 --> 00:20:26,760
- A real date, aren't you scared?

385
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:27,963
- Scared of what?

386
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:30,456
He's already kissed me.

387
00:20:30,456 --> 00:20:33,123
(group gasping)

388
00:20:35,178 --> 00:20:36,630
Hey, you're getting
your (indistinct) juice

389
00:20:36,630 --> 00:20:38,890
all over my shoe!

390
00:20:38,890 --> 00:20:40,530
- Gabby, wait, don't move,

391
00:20:40,530 --> 00:20:43,389
you have a big black
bug right in your eye.

392
00:20:43,389 --> 00:20:44,222
- A bug?

393
00:20:45,247 --> 00:20:48,652
That's not a bug, that's mascara.

394
00:20:48,652 --> 00:20:49,818
(group laughing)

395
00:20:49,818 --> 00:20:51,318
- [Lupe] Cover up.

396
00:21:04,034 --> 00:21:08,289
- Look, there's that
gorgeous cousin of Gabby's.

397
00:21:08,289 --> 00:21:09,830
Is he gonna stay around?

398
00:21:09,830 --> 00:21:11,470
- Oh, he just sort of popped up.

399
00:21:11,470 --> 00:21:14,440
No plans, no suitcase, and no manner.

400
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:15,750
- Aren't ya gonna introduce us?

401
00:21:15,750 --> 00:21:17,713
It's only polite.

402
00:21:35,374 --> 00:21:38,020
(Announcer speaking in foreign language)

403
00:21:38,020 --> 00:21:38,873
- Ramon.

404
00:21:38,873 --> 00:21:42,336
(Announcer speaking in foreign language)

405
00:21:42,336 --> 00:21:45,420
(upbeat music)
(singing in foreign language)

406
00:21:45,420 --> 00:21:49,300
These are my very good friends
Jackie, Lupe, and Marta.

407
00:21:50,423 --> 00:21:52,060
- What's up?

408
00:21:52,060 --> 00:21:56,400
- You remember Marta, you danced
with her at Gabby's quince.

409
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:58,450
- Yes, I remember her.

410
00:21:58,450 --> 00:22:00,977
- Well, aren't ya gonna
ask her to dance now?

411
00:22:02,451 --> 00:22:04,105
- Did you bring your
father with you this time?

412
00:22:04,105 --> 00:22:05,105
- No.

413
00:22:05,105 --> 00:22:08,856
(singing in foreign language)

414
00:22:08,856 --> 00:22:11,606
(Gabby cheering)

415
00:22:21,940 --> 00:22:23,430
- Where'd you learn how to dance?

416
00:22:23,430 --> 00:22:25,280
- On the top of my
father's shoes, and you?

417
00:22:25,280 --> 00:22:26,560
- Hey, everybody's good at somethin'.

418
00:22:26,560 --> 00:22:27,393
This is what I know how to do.

419
00:22:27,393 --> 00:22:29,730
- So I hear you're from New York?

420
00:22:29,730 --> 00:22:30,563
- PR.

421
00:22:30,563 --> 00:22:32,250
- What?
- Puerto Rico.

422
00:22:32,250 --> 00:22:34,080
- And now you live here
with your aunt or something.

423
00:22:34,080 --> 00:22:35,310
- Hey look, let me tell you somethin',

424
00:22:35,310 --> 00:22:37,520
I've been taking care of myself
since I was 14, all right.

425
00:22:37,520 --> 00:22:39,703
- 14, that's my age.

426
00:22:44,521 --> 00:22:47,190
- Who's Richard Stands?

427
00:22:47,190 --> 00:22:48,078
- Who?

428
00:22:48,078 --> 00:22:49,495
- Richard Stands.

429
00:22:50,949 --> 00:22:52,900
- One of your little friends at school.

430
00:22:52,900 --> 00:22:56,190
- No, in the morning when we
say the Pledge of Allegiance,

431
00:22:56,190 --> 00:22:59,653
you say and to the republic
for Richard Stands.

432
00:23:01,950 --> 00:23:02,850
- Richards Stands.

433
00:23:04,740 --> 00:23:05,573
He must be one of the-

434
00:23:05,573 --> 00:23:08,877
- There's no Richards Stands, stupid.

435
00:23:08,877 --> 00:23:12,300
It's to the republic for which it stands.

436
00:23:12,300 --> 00:23:14,920
- Hey, that's an easy mistake.

437
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:17,480
And don't call your brother stupid.

438
00:23:17,480 --> 00:23:20,073
- Hey, Pop, wanna help me
with my stamp collection?

439
00:23:21,243 --> 00:23:22,798
- I'm gonna go for walk.

440
00:23:22,798 --> 00:23:25,805
(lively music)

441
00:23:25,805 --> 00:23:29,638
(singing in foreign language)

442
00:23:48,764 --> 00:23:51,690
- Come on, Marta, we gotta
go, it's almost 10 o'clock.

443
00:23:51,690 --> 00:23:53,278
I'm gonna be in big trouble.

444
00:23:53,278 --> 00:23:54,633
- What?

445
00:23:54,633 --> 00:23:56,383
- We've gotta go now!

446
00:23:57,746 --> 00:24:00,413
- Come on, come on, wait,
stay for this dance, huh.

447
00:24:00,413 --> 00:24:02,415
- No, I can't be late.

448
00:24:02,415 --> 00:24:03,340
- I'll tell you what,

449
00:24:03,340 --> 00:24:05,773
if you stay I'll take you
home in my car, all right.

450
00:24:11,698 --> 00:24:14,439
All right, all right, all of you.

451
00:24:14,439 --> 00:24:15,606
- It's a deal.

452
00:24:29,451 --> 00:24:31,613
(playful music)

453
00:24:31,613 --> 00:24:34,230
- Are we all gonna fit in your car?

454
00:24:34,230 --> 00:24:35,270
- Well, if you don't,

455
00:24:35,270 --> 00:24:37,755
what we gotta do is just
all squeeze in together.

456
00:24:37,755 --> 00:24:40,901
(group laughing)

457
00:24:40,901 --> 00:24:42,413
- Marta, isn't that your dad?

458
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:49,890
- Papi, what are you doing?

459
00:24:49,890 --> 00:24:52,190
- I was out for a walk, it's getting late,

460
00:24:52,190 --> 00:24:54,540
I thought it'd be a good
idea to walk you home.

461
00:24:56,460 --> 00:24:57,660
- See you guys tomorrow.

462
00:24:58,880 --> 00:24:59,843
- Goodnight, Mr. Delacruz.

463
00:24:59,843 --> 00:25:01,033
- Bye, Mr. Delacruz.

464
00:25:02,450 --> 00:25:03,633
- Goodnight, girls.

465
00:25:10,413 --> 00:25:12,013
What were you girls doing with that boy?

466
00:25:12,900 --> 00:25:14,333
- He's just Gabby's cousin.

467
00:25:15,361 --> 00:25:16,511
- How old is he anyway?

468
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:19,580
I think he's too old mija.

469
00:25:22,300 --> 00:25:23,400
Think you're too young.

470
00:25:23,400 --> 00:25:24,850
- [Marta] I'm not too young, Papi.

471
00:25:24,850 --> 00:25:26,940
Other girls my age are already dating.

472
00:25:26,940 --> 00:25:28,013
- [Samuel] That's enough.

473
00:25:31,594 --> 00:25:36,594
(singing in foreign language)
(upbeat music)

474
00:25:40,030 --> 00:25:41,419
Cherry, cherry.

475
00:25:41,419 --> 00:25:42,669
- Yeah, cherry.

476
00:25:45,060 --> 00:25:48,283
- Papi, (speaks in
foreign language) Jorge.

477
00:25:48,283 --> 00:25:49,426
Jorge, Jorge.

478
00:25:49,426 --> 00:25:50,695
- Richardo.

479
00:25:50,695 --> 00:25:51,643
(speaks in foreign language) Samuel.

480
00:25:52,645 --> 00:25:53,799
(Samuel speaks in foreign language)

481
00:25:53,799 --> 00:25:54,994
(Jorge speaks in foreign language)

482
00:25:54,994 --> 00:25:55,930
- Que pasa?

483
00:25:55,930 --> 00:25:58,880
- I look for work, but
they ask me for paper,

484
00:25:58,880 --> 00:26:02,290
so I buy false card, it's no good.

485
00:26:02,290 --> 00:26:03,190
The boss, he no take it.

486
00:26:03,190 --> 00:26:05,970
- Papi.
- I'm sorry, Jorge.

487
00:26:05,970 --> 00:26:09,340
I wish I could help, but
it's the same at the factory.

488
00:26:09,340 --> 00:26:10,290
All you can do is keep trying.

489
00:26:10,290 --> 00:26:13,503
- I just want to work and earn my way.

490
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:15,880
- It's what we all want.

491
00:26:17,620 --> 00:26:19,656
- Hey, baseball, huh, Dodgers.

492
00:26:19,656 --> 00:26:20,489
- Yeah.

493
00:26:21,770 --> 00:26:23,320
Hey, Ricardo, this is dripping.

494
00:26:25,180 --> 00:26:26,570
- You do it.
- No, you do it.

495
00:26:26,570 --> 00:26:27,810
- You do it best, Marta.

496
00:26:27,810 --> 00:26:29,010
- But we all work with these people now.

497
00:26:29,010 --> 00:26:31,110
- Oh, Mrs. Zavala said, "Their
days are numbered anyway."

498
00:26:31,110 --> 00:26:32,360
- Come on, Marta, just do it.

499
00:26:32,360 --> 00:26:33,193
- All right.

500
00:26:36,863 --> 00:26:38,280
- Go, just do it.

501
00:26:41,416 --> 00:26:44,616
(Marta speaking in foreign language)

502
00:26:44,616 --> 00:26:46,077
(girls laughing)

503
00:26:46,077 --> 00:26:49,693
(man speaking in foreign language)

504
00:26:49,693 --> 00:26:51,700
- How about another
one for my friend, huh?

505
00:26:51,700 --> 00:26:53,463
- Gracias.
- Here you go.

506
00:26:54,612 --> 00:26:56,023
(man speaking in foreign language)

507
00:26:56,023 --> 00:26:58,773
(dramatic music)

508
00:27:06,426 --> 00:27:08,147
Come on mijo, let's go.

509
00:27:08,147 --> 00:27:10,897
(girls laughing)

510
00:27:18,800 --> 00:27:22,890
Come on, it was different in
our day, we went unnoticed.

511
00:27:22,890 --> 00:27:24,570
The days (speaks in foreign language)

512
00:27:24,570 --> 00:27:26,660
are brazen like roosters.

513
00:27:26,660 --> 00:27:27,493
They're asking for trouble.

514
00:27:27,493 --> 00:27:31,130
- Samuel, you are so hard.

515
00:27:31,130 --> 00:27:32,627
- [Samuel] Am I wrong, Inez?

516
00:27:32,627 --> 00:27:33,740
(speaks in foreign
language) On the Boulevard

517
00:27:33,740 --> 00:27:35,090
on a nice Saturday afternoon.

518
00:27:35,090 --> 00:27:37,870
Now tell me that isn't
because of the roosters.

519
00:27:37,870 --> 00:27:39,223
- We saw them at Chan's.

520
00:27:41,730 --> 00:27:44,680
- Ricky, do me a favor,
take this food to Jorge.

521
00:27:44,680 --> 00:27:45,513
- I'll take it.

522
00:27:50,869 --> 00:27:52,020
(door bell buzzes)

523
00:27:52,020 --> 00:27:54,410
- Hello, is your mother home?

524
00:27:54,410 --> 00:27:55,243
- Mama.

525
00:27:56,290 --> 00:27:59,580
- Oh, I meant your
mother, not your sister.

526
00:27:59,580 --> 00:28:01,510
Which one of you is having the
(speaks in foreign language)?

