00:44:03,530 --> 00:44:04,363
- Sure.

788
00:44:07,450 --> 00:44:08,908
(upbeat rock music)

789
00:44:08,908 --> 00:44:11,158
- Is that too loud for you?

790
00:44:21,237 --> 00:44:22,070
(tires screeching)

791
00:44:22,070 --> 00:44:24,337
- Marta, what do I tell them?

792
00:44:24,337 --> 00:44:26,004
- Whatever you want!

793
00:44:29,663 --> 00:44:31,240
- She's heartbroken.

794
00:44:31,240 --> 00:44:33,557
It was her favorite uncle.

795
00:44:33,557 --> 00:44:34,550
(group gasps)

796
00:44:34,550 --> 00:44:36,530
At least he went peacefully in his sleep.

797
00:44:36,530 --> 00:44:38,983
- Oh, wow, it's so tragic.

798
00:44:40,020 --> 00:44:42,300
- She can't possibly have her quince now,

799
00:44:42,300 --> 00:44:44,504
the whole family's in mourning.

800
00:44:44,504 --> 00:44:46,170
- (gasps) Poor Marta.

801
00:44:46,170 --> 00:44:47,403
She must be so sad.

802
00:45:29,171 --> 00:45:30,220
- [Marta] Are you sure I'm not gonna fall?

803
00:45:30,220 --> 00:45:31,430
- I'm not gonna let you fall.

804
00:45:31,430 --> 00:45:32,820
Look all you gotta do is put one foot

805
00:45:32,820 --> 00:45:34,470
in front of the other, like this.

806
00:45:35,840 --> 00:45:37,297
- This is dangerous.

807
00:45:37,297 --> 00:45:38,947
- I know, that's the whole point.

808
00:45:39,910 --> 00:45:40,910
- Should we be here?

809
00:45:41,820 --> 00:45:43,907
That sign says, "No trespassing."

810
00:45:45,590 --> 00:45:49,053
- Yeah, from that side
doesn't say anything.

811
00:45:51,430 --> 00:45:52,807
Oh, come on, will you chill out, please.

812
00:45:52,807 --> 00:45:55,718
I mean I come here every
night under the full moon.

813
00:45:55,718 --> 00:45:58,990
(imitates wolf howling)

814
00:45:58,990 --> 00:46:01,243
- There isn't a full moon every night.

815
00:46:02,580 --> 00:46:04,610
- Don't you know when I'm bragging.

816
00:46:04,610 --> 00:46:05,860
- You're always bragging,

817
00:46:05,860 --> 00:46:08,563
so I know when you're
bragging, it's all the time.

818
00:46:10,250 --> 00:46:11,383
- You're right.

819
00:46:13,870 --> 00:46:15,020
Come on, wait a second.

820
00:46:16,110 --> 00:46:17,193
Come on, Marta, wait.

821
00:46:18,210 --> 00:46:20,190
Hey, hey, hey, come on.

822
00:46:20,190 --> 00:46:21,023
Come here, what are you doing?

823
00:46:21,023 --> 00:46:23,044
What are you crazy or something?

824
00:46:23,044 --> 00:46:23,877
If I'm gonna be your escort

825
00:46:23,877 --> 00:46:25,690
I can't let nothing bad
happen to you, come on.

826
00:46:25,690 --> 00:46:27,430
- Ah, Ramon, there's
something I have to tell you.

827
00:46:27,430 --> 00:46:28,860
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, I know,

828
00:46:28,860 --> 00:46:32,220
you just don't want your
girlfriends to die of jealousy.

829
00:46:32,220 --> 00:46:35,083
Marta Delacruz, may I have
the honor of this dance?

830
00:46:36,230 --> 00:46:37,063
- Yes.

831
00:46:38,015 --> 00:46:41,098
(upbeat salsa music)

832
00:46:43,540 --> 00:46:44,980
I wanna lead.

833
00:46:44,980 --> 00:46:46,760
- Hey, wait, wait, wait,
that's supposed to be my job.

834
00:46:46,760 --> 00:46:47,900
- My job now.

835
00:46:47,900 --> 00:46:49,800
- Fine you wanna lead, okay, you lead.

836
00:46:52,440 --> 00:46:53,403
Now it's my turn.

837
00:47:04,756 --> 00:47:09,173
I told you I wasn't gonna
let anything happen to you.

838
00:47:12,753 --> 00:47:13,920
- [Group] Ooh.

839
00:47:15,090 --> 00:47:16,840
- Marta, I'm telling.

840
00:47:18,763 --> 00:47:20,640
- You little twerp.

841
00:47:20,640 --> 00:47:21,920
I gotta go.

842
00:47:21,920 --> 00:47:23,252
- Wait, wait a minute.

843
00:47:23,252 --> 00:47:25,919
(kids giggling)

844
00:47:31,529 --> 00:47:34,612
(upbeat piano music)

845
00:47:35,976 --> 00:47:37,390
- You better not tell anyone.

846
00:47:37,390 --> 00:47:38,500
- Give me a radio.

847
00:47:38,500 --> 00:47:39,333
- No way.

848
00:47:39,333 --> 00:47:40,290
- Then I'm gonna tell.

849
00:47:40,290 --> 00:47:41,123
- No you're not.

850
00:47:44,259 --> 00:47:45,481
- [Eddie] Let me out, Marta!

851
00:47:45,481 --> 00:47:46,863
I'm gonna get you!

852
00:47:46,863 --> 00:47:47,696
Let me out!

853
00:47:47,696 --> 00:47:49,121
- You're grounded young lady.
- Get me out of here!

854
00:47:49,121 --> 00:47:50,097
- But Papi.

855
00:47:50,097 --> 00:47:53,800
- But nothing, school, church,
and home, and that's it.

856
00:47:53,800 --> 00:47:56,480
- That's not fair, if
you would only trust me.

857
00:47:56,480 --> 00:47:59,843
- Trust is something you
earn, you don't deserve it.

858
00:48:02,330 --> 00:48:03,680
And let your brother out.

859
00:48:03,680 --> 00:48:05,160
He didn't need to tell me,

860
00:48:05,160 --> 00:48:06,660
I saw you myself from the bus.

861
00:48:17,520 --> 00:48:19,560
She deliberately disobeyed me.

862
00:48:19,560 --> 00:48:21,020
- She's disappointed, Samuel.

863
00:48:21,020 --> 00:48:22,800
Try to understand.

864
00:48:22,800 --> 00:48:25,370
- No, Inez, she has to understand,

865
00:48:25,370 --> 00:48:27,610
I am still the head of this family.

866
00:48:27,610 --> 00:48:31,370
- Samuel, Marta is becoming a young woman.

867
00:48:31,370 --> 00:48:33,260
You have to face reality.

868
00:48:33,260 --> 00:48:35,600
You can't stop things by ignoring them,

869
00:48:35,600 --> 00:48:38,200
not with her, not with your
job, not with any of it.

870
00:48:39,947 --> 00:48:42,530
(gentle music)

871
00:48:44,649 --> 00:48:45,740
(group chattering)

872
00:48:45,740 --> 00:48:47,840
- Arturo, this is bad.

873
00:48:47,840 --> 00:48:49,960
These need to be shipped by Thursday.

874
00:48:49,960 --> 00:48:50,850
We need more men.

875
00:48:50,850 --> 00:48:51,870
- I know that.

876
00:48:51,870 --> 00:48:53,690
I'm filling in for half the crew myself.

877
00:48:53,690 --> 00:48:55,340
- I'm still waiting to put
through your clearance.

878
00:48:55,340 --> 00:48:57,090
How many times do I have to ask ya?

879
00:48:58,870 --> 00:48:59,863
- I'm sorry, sir.

880
00:49:00,730 --> 00:49:05,270
It's just a situation of misplaced papers.

881
00:49:05,270 --> 00:49:07,010
We've moved so many times.

882
00:49:07,010 --> 00:49:10,210
- Then go down to the social
security office and get a copy.

883
00:49:10,210 --> 00:49:11,374
They got a file, you know.

884
00:49:11,374 --> 00:49:12,207
- Yeah.

885
00:49:13,660 --> 00:49:18,223
Mr. Waterman, you have to
give me a little time, please.

886
00:49:19,860 --> 00:49:22,010
- I don't wanna hear, I don't wanna know.

887
00:49:22,010 --> 00:49:24,020
Put it this way my friend,

888
00:49:24,020 --> 00:49:26,093
without papers you don't work here.

889
00:49:33,213 --> 00:49:34,360
- Marta, where did you go?

890
00:49:34,360 --> 00:49:36,260
I was so worried about you.

891
00:49:36,260 --> 00:49:37,410
- Oh, there's nothing to worry about.

892
00:49:37,410 --> 00:49:39,432
We just went to the railroad tracks.

893
00:49:39,432 --> 00:49:40,507
- Marta.

894
00:49:40,507 --> 00:49:43,840
- Oh, Marta, it's so
terrible, I feel really bad.

895
00:49:43,840 --> 00:49:45,160
- She knows I'm grounded.

896
00:49:45,160 --> 00:49:46,070
- I don't think so.

897
00:49:46,070 --> 00:49:49,097
- (speaks in foreign language),
I heard about your uncle.

898
00:49:49,097 --> 00:49:52,670
(speaking in foreign language)

899
00:49:52,670 --> 00:49:54,040
- My uncle?

900
00:49:54,040 --> 00:49:56,100
- I told them he died.

901
00:49:56,100 --> 00:49:57,720
- Jackie, I'm in enough trouble

902
00:49:57,720 --> 00:49:59,893
as it is already, now this lie.

903
00:50:01,033 --> 00:50:03,300
- (sighs) Life is so short,

904
00:50:03,300 --> 00:50:05,563
I guess we have to party
while there's still time.

905
00:50:10,550 --> 00:50:11,700
- What do I have to do?

906
00:50:12,770 --> 00:50:16,050
- Prove that you've worked
steadily all these years.

907
00:50:16,050 --> 00:50:20,620
- Proof, these hands are my proof.

908
00:50:20,620 --> 00:50:22,470
What do they think I've
been doing all this time,

909
00:50:22,470 --> 00:50:23,623
sitting on my behind?

910
00:50:24,800 --> 00:50:27,000
- You've used different names, Samuel.

911
00:50:27,000 --> 00:50:28,730
Your past employers are the only ones

912
00:50:28,730 --> 00:50:30,180
who knew you by those names.

913
00:50:30,180 --> 00:50:33,360
- Father, do you really think
they're going to remember me

914
00:50:33,360 --> 00:50:35,570
from all the hundreds of others?

915
00:50:35,570 --> 00:50:39,178
And once I go and humiliate
myself in front of these people

916
00:50:39,178 --> 00:50:42,290
how do I know it's just not
another immigration trap?

917
00:50:42,290 --> 00:50:45,230
I've done this already you know, twice.

918
00:50:45,230 --> 00:50:46,870
- There's always that risk.

919
00:50:46,870 --> 00:50:50,630
But if you don't apply you will
never have your citizenship,

920
00:50:50,630 --> 00:50:52,473
and time is running out.

921
00:50:58,800 --> 00:51:03,323
- Nobody knows, not my
boss, not my friends,

922
00:51:05,190 --> 00:51:06,390
not even my children.

923
00:51:06,390 --> 00:51:08,790
- There are so many
others in your situation.

924
00:51:08,790 --> 00:51:11,020
- I am not like the others,

925
00:51:11,020 --> 00:51:14,650
I own my own house, I have a
secretary who takes my calls,

926
00:51:14,650 --> 00:51:16,373
I even have my own parking space.

927
00:51:17,350 --> 00:51:19,550
I'm not just some illegal.

928
00:51:19,550 --> 00:51:22,800
- Unless you have
amnesty, Samuel, you are.

929
00:51:22,800 --> 00:51:25,470
The bottom line is you have no choice.

930
00:51:25,470 --> 00:51:28,503
- No choice, well, we'll see about that.

931
00:51:29,716 --> 00:51:32,466
(dramatic music)

932
00:51:37,030 --> 00:51:39,300
- Don't be angry, Marta,
it's your own fault.

933
00:51:39,300 --> 00:51:40,610
- I never told you to lie.

934
00:51:40,610 --> 00:51:42,140
- Hey Marta, where are you going?

935
00:51:42,140 --> 00:51:43,370
- [Marta] Get away from me.

936
00:51:43,370 --> 00:51:46,740
- Just don't get too chummy
with your new boyfriend

937
00:51:46,740 --> 00:51:48,590
because we're gonna be gone.

938
00:51:48,590 --> 00:51:50,410
- What are you talking about?

939
00:51:50,410 --> 00:51:51,720
- Pop's taking us away.

940
00:51:51,720 --> 00:51:53,243
We're gonna raise horses.

941
00:51:56,742 --> 00:51:58,290
- [Jackie] Uh-oh.

942
00:51:58,290 --> 00:51:59,260
- How ya doing?

943
00:51:59,260 --> 00:52:00,093
You want a ride?

944
00:52:00,093 --> 00:52:01,370
- Come on, Marta, let's go.

945
00:52:06,690 --> 00:52:08,253
Marta, let's go.

946
00:52:09,719 --> 00:52:10,552
- Pop.

947
00:52:11,900 --> 00:52:12,733
- Let's go home.

948
00:52:14,382 --> 00:52:16,965
(gentle music)

949
00:52:20,521 --> 00:52:21,354
- Come on.

950
00:52:22,470 --> 00:52:23,878
(dramatic music)

951
00:52:23,878 --> 00:52:24,711
- Papi.

952
00:52:29,640 --> 00:52:30,930
- We're leaving.
- Hooray,

953
00:52:30,930 --> 00:52:32,651
we're going to Mexico.

954
00:52:32,651 --> 00:52:33,484
- Mexico?

955
00:52:35,720 --> 00:52:37,625
- Come on, wait a second.
- Papi.

956
00:52:37,625 --> 00:52:39,310
(Samuel speaks in foreign language)

957
00:52:39,310 --> 00:52:40,628
- Come on, Marta, wait.

958
00:52:40,628 --> 00:52:45,128
(Samuel speaking in foreign language)

959
00:52:49,530 --> 00:52:52,310
- If we move down to Mexico
that'll be the end of my life.

960
00:52:52,310 --> 00:52:54,930
- Well, does your father
say you're really going?

961
00:52:54,930 --> 00:52:57,620
- I don't know he hardly
says anything to me anymore.

962
00:52:57,620 --> 00:52:59,350
- Have you seen Ramon?

963
00:52:59,350 --> 00:53:02,010
Does he know that the
party's been canceled?

964
00:53:02,010 --> 00:53:03,420
Uh-oh.

965
00:53:03,420 --> 00:53:06,420
- How can I even see him, I'm
not allowed out of the house?

966
00:53:06,420 --> 00:53:07,720
- Poor Marta.

967
00:53:07,720 --> 00:53:10,110
Don't worry, things don't get better,

968
00:53:10,110 --> 00:53:11,310
they can only get worse.

969
00:53:14,484 --> 00:53:17,067
(gentle music)

970
00:53:29,225 --> 00:53:31,808
(gentle music)

971
00:53:43,908 --> 00:53:46,991
(upbeat salsa music)

972
00:54:09,010 --> 00:54:09,843
- Mom.

973
00:54:09,843 --> 00:54:12,350
- Huh?
- There's no milk left.

974
00:54:12,350 --> 00:54:15,430
- [Inez] Yes, there is,
Marta, in the carton.

975
00:54:15,430 --> 00:54:16,840
- It's empty.

976
00:54:16,840 --> 00:54:18,350
I can go get some.

977
00:54:18,350 --> 00:54:22,030
- [Inez] All right, but
hurry up, you know the rules.

978
00:54:22,030 --> 00:54:25,113
(upbeat salsa music)

979
00:54:38,455 --> 00:54:40,788
- I'm gonna put her caps on.

980
00:54:46,230 --> 00:54:47,270
- Hi.

981
00:54:47,270 --> 00:54:49,266
- Hey, come here, I
gotta show you something.

982
00:54:49,266 --> 00:54:51,766
Here, go, go, go, go, come on.

983
00:54:53,128 --> 00:54:55,252
Check this out, I've been
practicing, right, hold that.

984
00:54:55,252 --> 00:54:56,396
Watch this.

985
00:54:56,396 --> 00:54:58,896
Da-da-de-de-de-de-de-de-da-da.

986
00:55:00,536 --> 00:55:01,920
Yo, we're gonna kill 'em.

987
00:55:01,920 --> 00:55:03,720
- Well, actually we do a waltz.

988
00:55:03,720 --> 00:55:05,100
- A waltz?

989
00:55:05,100 --> 00:55:06,580
Come on, can't we jazz it up a little bit.

990
00:55:06,580 --> 00:55:08,040
I mean what is it a funeral?

991
00:55:08,040 --> 00:55:12,637
- No, it's an honor court,
and you and I would waltz.

992
00:55:12,637 --> 00:55:13,780
- You (indistinct) are somethin' else.

993
00:55:13,780 --> 00:55:15,360
A waltz?

994
00:55:15,360 --> 00:55:16,790
I mean I just a brand new suit.

995
00:55:16,790 --> 00:55:18,930
I mean, I don't know what it's
gonna look like in a waltz.

996
00:55:18,930 --> 00:55:20,620
- Oh no, you have to take it back.

997
00:55:20,620 --> 00:55:21,453
- No way, what?

998
00:55:21,453 --> 00:55:24,050
What did you think you're
gonna escorted by some bum?

999
00:55:26,430 --> 00:55:28,680
All right, all right,
so we waltz, then what?

1000
00:55:30,570 --> 00:55:32,650
- Then there's a band, and lots of food,

1001
00:55:32,650 --> 00:55:34,310
and matching tablecloths,

1002
00:55:34,310 --> 00:55:35,950
and sometimes your name's up in lights.

1003
00:55:35,950 --> 00:55:37,910
- In lights, like a Broadway show?

1004
00:55:37,910 --> 00:55:40,090
Starring daddy's little girl.

1005
00:55:40,090 --> 00:55:41,800
- I'm not a little girl.
- Okay, okay, okay,

1006
00:55:41,800 --> 00:55:43,340
I'm sorry, you're not a little girl.

1007
00:55:43,340 --> 00:55:45,550
- I can earn a living just like you.

1008
00:55:45,550 --> 00:55:46,383
- A living?

1009
00:55:47,232 --> 00:55:49,832
Hey look, I change tires,
okay, that's not a living.

1010
00:55:51,060 --> 00:55:51,900
You don't know anything.

1011
00:55:51,900 --> 00:55:53,360
I mean it's survival out here.

1012
00:55:53,360 --> 00:55:55,810
It's not some fairy tale
with some fancy parties.

1013
00:55:56,900 --> 00:55:57,923
Don't do what I did.

1014
00:55:58,870 --> 00:56:00,130
Stay with your family, Marta, okay,

1015
00:56:00,130 --> 00:56:02,897
'cause that's the best thing you got.

1016
00:56:02,897 --> 00:56:04,083
(somber music)

1017
00:56:04,083 --> 00:56:07,390
- Why do you feel so sorry for yourself?

1018
00:56:07,390 --> 00:56:08,500
- Look Cinderella, you got no right

1019
00:56:08,500 --> 00:56:10,000
to talk to me like that, okay.

1020
00:56:12,340 --> 00:56:14,780
- You can do whatever
you set your mind to.

1021
00:56:14,780 --> 00:56:16,590
- You actually believe that garbage?

1022
00:56:16,590 --> 00:56:18,990
Who tells you that, your rich father?

1023
00:56:18,990 --> 00:56:20,520
Hey look, my life isn't
like yours all right.

1024
00:56:20,520 --> 00:56:21,700
I'm going nowhere.

1025
00:56:21,700 --> 00:56:23,960
I can't even read the
words on that milk carton.

1026
00:56:23,960 --> 00:56:25,310
- So you can learn.

1027
00:56:25,310 --> 00:56:26,170
- Forget about it, all right.

1028
00:56:26,170 --> 00:56:27,810
They've already pushed all
those kiddie books on me,

1029
00:56:27,810 --> 00:56:29,130
so just forget it!

1030
00:56:29,130 --> 00:56:29,963
- Ramon.

1031
00:56:34,420 --> 00:56:39,420
- Look, you feel something
inside you about who you are,

1032
00:56:40,720 --> 00:56:44,200
your place in this world,
me, I can't feel that.

1033
00:56:49,470 --> 00:56:53,063
It's like a wall and I
keep trying to get over it,

1034
00:56:54,930 --> 00:56:57,750
so instead I just keep crashing into it.

1035
00:56:57,750 --> 00:56:59,343
- So go around it.

1036
00:57:01,516 --> 00:57:02,573
- You're such a kid.

1037
00:57:04,820 --> 00:57:06,770
You know you need me to be your escort.

1038
00:57:07,620 --> 00:57:09,793
Between all your friends,
what they're 12-years-old.

1039
00:57:10,810 --> 00:57:12,050
If you don't have me there it's gonna turn

1040
00:57:12,050 --> 00:57:14,110
into "The Mickey Mouse Club".

1041
00:57:14,110 --> 00:57:14,943
- You're right.

1042
00:57:18,586 --> 00:57:19,436
- So we still on?

1043
00:57:21,110 --> 00:57:22,700
I mean it's not too late, right?

1044
00:57:22,700 --> 00:57:23,890
- Late!

1045
00:57:23,890 --> 00:57:24,930
What time is it?

1046
00:57:24,930 --> 00:57:25,763
I gotta go.

1047
00:57:25,763 --> 00:57:26,940
- [Ramon] Hey, wait a minute,
how come you're always

1048
00:57:26,940 --> 00:57:27,990
running away from me?

1049
00:57:30,130 --> 00:57:32,713
(gentle music)

1050
00:57:40,370 --> 00:57:42,070
- I sent her out over an hour ago.

1051
00:57:44,770 --> 00:57:47,363
- This food is cold,
we've waited long enough.

1052
00:57:49,170 --> 00:57:51,056
- Rice and beans again.

1053
00:57:51,056 --> 00:57:54,120
- (sighs) Chang's not
giving any more credit,

1054
00:57:54,120 --> 00:57:57,270
I had to put back some of
the food I couldn't afford.

1055
00:57:57,270 --> 00:57:58,590
- Don't worry, (speaks
in foreign language).

1056
00:57:59,751 --> 00:58:02,055
This is good basic food.

1057
00:58:02,055 --> 00:58:05,510
A man could live forever on
rice and beans, right Eddie?

1058
00:58:05,510 --> 00:58:10,056
- Uh, I rather live
forever on french fries.

1059
00:58:10,056 --> 00:58:13,639
(Inez and Samuel laughing)

1060
00:58:16,292 --> 00:58:18,070
- Ah, it's about time.

1061
00:58:18,070 --> 00:58:19,720
Put the milk on the table, Marta.

1062
00:58:23,560 --> 00:58:24,911
You've been gone all this time

1063
00:58:24,911 --> 00:58:26,603
and you don't have the milk, huh?

1064
00:58:27,960 --> 00:58:29,290
We'll talk about this later.

1065
00:58:29,290 --> 00:58:31,543
- No, we'll talk about this now.

1066
00:58:33,010 --> 00:58:34,050
- They were all out of milk at Chang's

1067
00:58:34,050 --> 00:58:35,130
and I had to go all over the place

1068
00:58:35,130 --> 00:58:36,310
to find another store with milk,

1069
00:58:36,310 --> 00:58:37,470
and some of 'em were closed,

1070
00:58:37,470 --> 00:58:38,963
and I couldn't find-
- Stop.

1071
00:58:40,030 --> 00:58:41,173
You insult us.

1072
00:58:42,518 --> 00:58:43,793
A Delacruz does not lie.

1073
00:58:45,610 --> 00:58:47,160
Were you with that boy?

1074
00:58:47,160 --> 00:58:49,160
- What do you have against him?

1075
00:58:49,160 --> 00:58:50,523
- Don't talk back to me.

1076
00:58:51,380 --> 00:58:53,250
I ask the questions here.

1077
00:58:53,250 --> 00:58:55,380
Do you think you can disobey?

1078
00:58:55,380 --> 00:58:56,970
Go against your father.

1079
00:58:56,970 --> 00:58:57,803
- No.

1080
00:59:01,676 --> 00:59:05,810
(Samuel speaking in foreign language)

1081
00:59:05,810 --> 00:59:07,350
- Pass me the bread.

1082
00:59:07,350 --> 00:59:09,743
Are have you stopped
understanding your native tongue?

1083
00:59:10,940 --> 00:59:12,934
- My native tongue is English.

1084
00:59:12,934 --> 00:59:15,684
(dramatic music)

1085
00:59:17,276 --> 00:59:21,890
(Inez speaks in foreign language)

1086
00:59:21,890 --> 00:59:25,313
I was born here so my
native tongue is English.

1087
00:59:29,210 --> 00:59:30,630
- Do you think you're better than those

1088
00:59:30,630 --> 00:59:32,730
who weren't fortunate enough to come here?

1089
00:59:35,050 --> 00:59:36,120
Do you?

1090
00:59:36,120 --> 00:59:36,953
- Do you?

1091
00:59:37,950 --> 00:59:38,783
- Samuel!

1092
00:59:47,260 --> 00:59:49,117
What is happening to this family?

1093
00:59:56,164 --> 00:59:58,997
(rooster crowing)

1094
01:00:01,128 --> 01:00:04,210
- Samuel, (speaks in foreign language).

1095
01:00:04,210 --> 01:00:06,390
You walk to work to
save your pennies, huh?

1096
01:00:06,390 --> 01:00:07,835
- Ah, my car broke down again.

1097
01:00:07,835 --> 01:00:09,761
(Jorge speaks in foreign language)

1098
01:00:09,761 --> 01:00:10,830
(Samuel speaks in foreign language)

1099
01:00:10,830 --> 01:00:14,060
- I have job and they no ask me for paper.

1100
01:00:14,060 --> 01:00:15,350
- Really, that's terrific.

1101
01:00:15,350 --> 01:00:17,380
I knew you would finds something.

1102
01:00:17,380 --> 01:00:18,310
And where is it?

1103
01:00:18,310 --> 01:00:20,530
- Delaware House on Broadway.

1104
01:00:20,530 --> 01:00:23,790
- Ay, Jorge, that place
will hire you for a week,

1105
01:00:23,790 --> 01:00:25,457
then come payday the call
(speaks in foreign language).

1106
01:00:26,576 --> 01:00:29,023
- I, I have to take a chance.

1107
01:00:31,072 --> 01:00:33,350
(Samuel speaks in foreign language)

1108
01:00:33,350 --> 01:00:35,639
- No, no, I'll take care of it.

1109
01:00:35,639 --> 01:00:37,061
Better days ahead.

1110
01:00:37,061 --> 01:00:40,801
(Jorge speaks in foreign language)

1111
01:00:40,801 --> 01:00:45,801
(Inez humming)
(upbeat music)

1112
01:00:51,483 --> 01:00:55,316
(singing in foreign language)

1113
01:01:17,050 --> 01:01:19,350
- The kids are asleep,
you won't be disturbed.

1114
01:01:22,830 --> 01:01:24,940
- I never meant for this
to become such a problem.

1115
01:01:24,940 --> 01:01:26,220
- I know, I know.

1116
01:01:30,186 --> 01:01:32,853
- Our whole life is in this box.

1117
01:01:36,760 --> 01:01:41,760
Last time I tried this they
said, "The slots were full."

1118
01:01:44,280 --> 01:01:47,513
And there I was with my tail hanging out.

1119
01:01:49,390 --> 01:01:50,700
- That lawyer was a crook,

1120
01:01:50,700 --> 01:01:52,400
he left you wide open for trouble.

1121
01:01:55,000 --> 01:01:57,820
- I kept thinking some day I'd try again

1122
01:01:57,820 --> 01:01:59,953
when I wouldn't have so much to lose.

1123
01:02:04,460 --> 01:02:05,960
Now I have everything to lose.

1124
01:02:08,500 --> 01:02:09,733
- So I guess it's time.

1125
01:02:11,556 --> 01:02:14,639
(upbeat salsa music)

1126
01:02:38,081 --> 01:02:40,303
(group chattering)

1127
01:02:40,303 --> 01:02:42,400
- (gasps) Ooh, remember this one.

1128
01:02:42,400 --> 01:02:46,150
Oh, my dad was so proud, his
speech lasted for 20 minutes.

1129
01:02:46,150 --> 01:02:47,250
- Look at your dress.

1130
01:02:47,250 --> 01:02:49,047
Marta, wasn't it beautiful?

1131
01:02:50,010 --> 01:02:51,710
- Can we get back to work, please?

1132
01:03:00,183 --> 01:03:03,183
(suspenseful music)

1133
01:03:33,442 --> 01:03:34,859
- Come in, Marta.

1134
01:03:38,520 --> 01:03:40,410
- What does it mean in these files

1135
01:03:40,410 --> 01:03:42,760
when the same person has two names?

1136
01:03:42,760 --> 01:03:45,150
- Usually it means that
they've been using false papers

1137
01:03:45,150 --> 01:03:48,420
and false names to work because
they don't have documents.

1138
01:03:48,420 --> 01:03:51,407
- But what if this person is
already an American citizen?

1139
01:03:51,407 --> 01:03:53,240
- Did you see the file in this office?

1140
01:03:53,240 --> 01:03:54,073
- Yes.

1141
01:03:54,073 --> 01:03:55,340
- If they were a citizen

1142
01:03:55,340 --> 01:03:57,290
they wouldn't be coming to this office.

1143
01:04:02,888 --> 01:04:05,888
(suspenseful music)

1144
01:04:58,951 --> 01:05:01,951
(door bell buzzing)

1145
01:05:04,263 --> 01:05:05,096
- Hey, how ya doing?

1146
01:05:05,096 --> 01:05:06,220
- What are you doing here?

1147
01:05:06,220 --> 01:05:07,660
How did you know where I live?

1148
01:05:07,660 --> 01:05:08,830
- Come here, I want you to
see something, all right.

1149
01:05:08,830 --> 01:05:10,080
Check this out.

1150
01:05:11,110 --> 01:05:13,100
I am now the new waltz king.

1151
01:05:16,819 --> 01:05:17,652
Ta-dah!

1152
01:05:17,652 --> 01:05:18,910
- Please, you can't stay here.

1153
01:05:18,910 --> 01:05:19,743
You have to be going.

1154
01:05:19,743 --> 01:05:20,850
Thanks for coming by.

1155
01:05:20,850 --> 01:05:22,030
- Hey, is this your car?

1156
01:05:22,030 --> 01:05:23,810
- Yeah, you want a ride?

1157
01:05:23,810 --> 01:05:26,540
Look, I'll even take
your sister too, okay.

1158
01:05:26,540 --> 01:05:28,910
Come on, let's go.
- No, please.

1159
01:05:28,910 --> 01:05:30,670
I can't come out now.

1160
01:05:30,670 --> 01:05:33,100
I have to stay inside,
my other brother is sick.

1161
01:05:33,100 --> 01:05:34,140
- Oh, come on, give me a break,

1162
01:05:34,140 --> 01:05:36,040
that is so lame, sick brother.

1163
01:05:36,040 --> 01:05:38,670
- Listen, I'm not having a party anymore.

1164
01:05:38,670 --> 01:05:40,300
It's been canceled, okay.

1165
01:05:40,300 --> 01:05:42,820
So there's no reason for us
to see each other anymore.

1166
01:05:42,820 --> 01:05:45,370
Now please, just go.

1167
01:05:45,370 --> 01:05:46,271
- Hold on a second here,

1168
01:05:46,271 --> 01:05:47,770
what are you talking about canceled?

1169
01:05:47,770 --> 01:05:48,603
What happened?

1170
01:05:48,603 --> 01:05:49,436
Did I do something wrong?

1171
01:05:49,436 --> 01:05:53,280
- No, yes, I don't know, I
don't know anything anymore.

1172
01:05:53,280 --> 01:05:55,380
Just please go away and leave me alone.

1173
01:05:55,380 --> 01:05:57,385
And don't come back here anymore!

1174
01:05:57,385 --> 01:05:58,871
- Hey, come on, wait a
second here, all right.

1175
01:05:58,871 --> 01:06:01,288
(door bangs)

1176
01:06:03,978 --> 01:06:04,978
Yo, back up.

1177
01:06:06,806 --> 01:06:09,889
(car engine revving)

1178
01:06:12,718 --> 01:06:15,718
(suspenseful music)

1179
01:06:26,340 --> 01:06:27,728
- [Secretary] King Wire Partitions.

1180
01:06:27,728 --> 01:06:29,447
- Arturo Montoya, please.

1181
01:06:29,447 --> 01:06:31,976
(phone buzzes)

1182
01:06:31,976 --> 01:06:34,476
- Art Montoya, can I help you?

1183
01:06:37,403 --> 01:06:39,258
- Eddie, drop your toys.

1184
01:06:39,258 --> 01:06:40,616
Come on it's time for dinner.

1185
01:06:40,616 --> 01:06:42,932
10 minutes (speaking in foreign language).

1186
01:06:42,932 --> 01:06:44,304
Don't forget.

1187
01:06:44,304 --> 01:06:46,721
10 minutes, Eddie, I mean it.

1188
01:06:54,500 --> 01:06:56,334
Don't forget that.

1189
01:06:56,334 --> 01:06:58,501
10 minutes, and I mean it.

1190
01:07:06,984 --> 01:07:09,151
This place is such a mess.

1191
01:07:11,449 --> 01:07:13,293
Are you all right?

1192
01:07:13,293 --> 01:07:15,903
- Why does Papi keep talking about Mexico?

1193
01:07:17,460 --> 01:07:19,810
- He doesn't talk about it that much.

1194
01:07:19,810 --> 01:07:22,450
- Is there any reason why we
might have to go down there?

1195
01:07:22,450 --> 01:07:24,600
- Of course not, we're
not moving anywhere.

1196
01:07:26,110 --> 01:07:28,390
- Is everyone in this
family an American citizen?

1197
01:07:28,390 --> 01:07:29,890
- Ay, mija, so many questions.

1198
01:07:31,943 --> 01:07:33,293
- Would you ever lie to me?

1199
01:07:36,670 --> 01:07:37,503
Nevermind.

1200
01:07:40,810 --> 01:07:41,660
- You got papers?

1201
01:07:42,870 --> 01:07:43,703
No papers.

1202
01:07:44,662 --> 01:07:46,562
No work without papers, you know that.

1203
01:07:47,400 --> 01:07:48,633
What's with you guys?

1204
01:07:49,560 --> 01:07:50,393
Next.

1205
01:07:51,275 --> 01:07:54,160
Okay, 4.50 an hour night shift
only, take it or leave it.

1206
01:07:54,160 --> 01:07:55,710
- That's not what I'm here for.

1207
01:07:58,182 --> 01:08:00,415
- You're a little overdressed
for this kind of work.

1208
01:08:00,415 --> 01:08:02,040
- I'd like to see the supervisor.

1209
01:08:02,040 --> 01:08:03,554
I have a private matter
to discuss with him.

1210
01:08:03,554 --> 01:08:05,570
- Whoa, private matter.

1211
01:08:05,570 --> 01:08:07,520
Well, we're not making
an exceptions today,

1212
01:08:07,520 --> 01:08:09,347
but that's a good try, I liked it.

1213
01:08:09,347 --> 01:08:11,350
- I'm not here for work.

1214
01:08:11,350 --> 01:08:12,930
- So then you're wasting my time.

1215
01:08:12,930 --> 01:08:14,670
Okay, next.
- Look, I am not one

1216
01:08:14,670 --> 01:08:16,420
of these newcomers.

1217
01:08:16,420 --> 01:08:17,890
I would like to talk to your supervisor.

1218
01:08:17,890 --> 01:08:19,900
- No way, Jose.

1219
01:08:19,900 --> 01:08:21,350
- Don't talk to me like that.

1220
01:08:22,403 --> 01:08:24,950
- I will talk to you anyway I like.

1221
01:08:24,950 --> 01:08:26,040
- I've been living in this country

1222
01:08:26,040 --> 01:08:27,208
since before you were in high school.

1223
01:08:27,208 --> 01:08:29,458
- Hey, get him out of here.

1224
01:08:35,509 --> 01:08:38,259
(birds chirping)

1225
01:08:45,120 --> 01:08:46,760
- Papi.

1226
01:08:46,760 --> 01:08:47,930
- What are doing out on the street?

1227
01:08:47,930 --> 01:08:48,970
You should be inside.

1228
01:08:48,970 --> 01:08:50,490
- Please, Papi, I have to talk to you.

1229
01:08:50,490 --> 01:08:52,220
- Ah, more business about this boy.

1230
01:08:52,220 --> 01:08:53,533
- No, it's not that.

1231
01:08:54,450 --> 01:08:56,913
Papi, I saw your file at work.

1232
01:08:57,835 --> 01:08:59,100
(light dramatic music)

1233
01:08:59,100 --> 01:09:00,243
I know about you.

1234
01:09:05,318 --> 01:09:07,235
Why didn't you tell me?

1235
01:09:08,130 --> 01:09:11,510
- Marta, this is none of your concern.

1236
01:09:11,510 --> 01:09:13,180
- Yes, it is, it's about all of us,

1237
01:09:13,180 --> 01:09:15,040
it's about me, and Ricky, and Eddie.

1238
01:09:15,040 --> 01:09:17,560
- Silence, since when does
a child tell the father.

1239
01:09:17,560 --> 01:09:20,960
- Is this why you were
talking about going to Mexico?

1240
01:09:20,960 --> 01:09:22,163
Are we being deported?

1241
01:09:23,800 --> 01:09:26,073
- Samuel Delacruz will
never be deported, mija.

1242
01:09:27,610 --> 01:09:29,810
If he leaves it will be
of his own free choice.

1243
01:09:29,810 --> 01:09:32,080
- Well, maybe we could
try and get some help.

1244
01:09:32,080 --> 01:09:33,136
Maybe I could do something.

1245
01:09:33,136 --> 01:09:34,270
- (speaks in foreign
language) There will be

1246
01:09:34,270 --> 01:09:37,333
no more conversations on this
to anyone, is that understood?

1247
01:09:38,210 --> 01:09:39,043
- Yes.

1248
01:09:42,792 --> 01:09:44,597
(Marta sighs)

1249
01:09:44,597 --> 01:09:46,283
(door bangs)

1250
01:09:46,283 --> 01:09:49,283
(suspenseful music)

1251
01:09:58,981 --> 01:10:03,231
(man speaking in foreign language)

1252
01:10:14,113 --> 01:10:14,946
- No!

1253
01:10:16,004 --> 01:10:16,837
No!

1254
01:10:18,835 --> 01:10:20,585
- Let's go, let's go!

1255
01:10:32,723 --> 01:10:34,143
- Jorge's been deported.

1256
01:10:35,140 --> 01:10:38,120
Carlos saw him get picked up
at the warehouse on Broadway.

1257
01:10:38,120 --> 01:10:40,110
- Jorge, will he be late?

1258
01:10:40,110 --> 01:10:42,330
- We won't be seeing Jorge anymore, honey.

1259
01:10:42,330 --> 01:10:44,060
- What's going on, what's happening?

1260
01:10:44,060 --> 01:10:45,250
- Get away from that window!

1261
01:10:45,250 --> 01:10:46,850
And if any immigration
officers come around

1262
01:10:46,850 --> 01:10:48,420
you don't know Jorge.

1263
01:10:48,420 --> 01:10:50,690
Now I want everybody to come
home right after school.

1264
01:10:50,690 --> 01:10:52,230
Stay close to the house,

1265
01:10:52,230 --> 01:10:54,230
and absolutely no taking to strangers.

1266
01:10:54,230 --> 01:10:56,823
- But they can't pick
us up, we're Americans.

1267
01:10:59,740 --> 01:11:01,893
- Just do as I say, understand?

1268
01:11:04,909 --> 01:11:07,492
(upbeat music)

1269
01:11:11,043 --> 01:11:14,876
(singing in foreign language)

1270
01:11:16,751 --> 01:11:20,584
(singing in foreign language)

1271
01:11:22,356 --> 01:11:26,189
(singing in foreign language)

1272
01:11:28,022 --> 01:11:31,855
(singing in foreign language)

1273
01:11:33,455 --> 01:11:37,288
(singing in foreign language)

1274
01:11:45,241 --> 01:11:49,074
(singing in foreign language)

1275
01:12:08,134 --> 01:12:11,967
(singing in foreign language)

1276
01:12:13,757 --> 01:12:17,590
(singing in foreign language)

1277
01:12:24,550 --> 01:12:26,770
- He doesn't have much time.

1278
01:12:26,770 --> 01:12:28,870
- He's doing the best he can.

1279
01:12:28,870 --> 01:12:31,850
- But what if he doesn't
get the signatures?

1280
01:12:31,850 --> 01:12:34,533
- Are you thinking about
him, us, or yourself?

1281
01:12:35,730 --> 01:12:38,293
- We're Americans, why
should we have to go?

1282
01:12:40,000 --> 01:12:43,323
- You're an American,
yes, you have privileges,

1283
01:12:44,180 --> 01:12:45,430
but I feel sorry for you.

1284
01:12:46,350 --> 01:12:48,950
Where you come from, what went before you,

1285
01:12:48,950 --> 01:12:50,720
you can't see that.

1286
01:12:50,720 --> 01:12:52,193
All you see is yourself.

1287
01:12:53,270 --> 01:12:56,830
Mommy, what things can I
get, what things can I have?

1288
01:12:56,830 --> 01:12:58,180
If that's being an American

1289
01:12:59,569 --> 01:13:01,519
then maybe we should go back to Mexico.

1290
01:13:06,047 --> 01:13:08,797
(dramatic music)

1291
01:13:10,236 --> 01:13:14,070
(school bell ringing)

1292
01:13:14,070 --> 01:13:16,100
- Marta, where have you been?

1293
01:13:16,100 --> 01:13:17,910
I haven't seen you in ages,

1294
01:13:17,910 --> 01:13:19,490
- Are you having your party or not?

1295
01:13:19,490 --> 01:13:21,120
- You heard about her uncle?

1296
01:13:21,120 --> 01:13:22,207
- Well, Ramon has just said,

1297
01:13:22,207 --> 01:13:24,240
"That her party has just been canceled."

1298
01:13:24,240 --> 01:13:26,030
But I thought it was
canceled a long time ago,

1299
01:13:26,030 --> 01:13:28,430
so what'd you do move it to a
