1423
01:21:18,860 --> 01:21:20,930
- Who's car is that?

1424
01:21:20,930 --> 01:21:21,763
- It's mine.

1425
01:21:23,710 --> 01:21:25,447
Come on, get in, all right, we gotta go.

1426
01:21:25,447 --> 01:21:28,197
(car door thuds)

1427
01:21:30,219 --> 01:21:33,302
(train bell ringing)

1428
01:21:43,520 --> 01:21:45,220
So this is where your old man works, huh?

1429
01:21:45,220 --> 01:21:46,730
- No, I could really
mess things up for him

1430
01:21:46,730 --> 01:21:48,300
if we went there.

1431
01:21:48,300 --> 01:21:50,400
We're working backwards from his last job.

1432
01:21:52,431 --> 01:21:55,120
Do I look old enough to be
taken seriously by these guys?

1433
01:21:55,120 --> 01:21:58,423
- You look great, but those
little socks they gotta go.

1434
01:22:00,341 --> 01:22:02,924
(gentle music)

1435
01:22:06,550 --> 01:22:08,127
A real woman.

1436
01:22:08,127 --> 01:22:09,864
If you need me I'm gonna
be right here, okay.

1437
01:22:09,864 --> 01:22:10,697
- Okay.

1438
01:22:11,870 --> 01:22:12,770
I'm going in there.

1439
01:22:12,770 --> 01:22:14,350
- [Ramon] Go for it.

1440
01:22:14,350 --> 01:22:15,783
- Okay, I'm ready.

1441
01:22:16,729 --> 01:22:18,062
- You can do it.

1442
01:22:20,177 --> 01:22:23,844
(light inspirational music)

1443
01:22:33,080 --> 01:22:33,923
Go around.

1444
01:22:36,530 --> 01:22:38,050
Around the corner.

1445
01:22:52,541 --> 01:22:56,791
(man speaking in foreign language)

1446
01:22:58,320 --> 01:23:00,210
- Come on, give me a break will ya.

1447
01:23:00,210 --> 01:23:01,927
Did I know that the truck
carrying the broken down parts

1448
01:23:01,927 --> 01:23:03,373
was gonna break down, huh?

1449
01:23:05,740 --> 01:23:08,880
Yeah, we're looking at
Friday, Monday maybe.

1450
01:23:08,880 --> 01:23:10,923
Right, next time we'll send 'em airmail.

1451
01:23:12,270 --> 01:23:13,103
Yeah.

1452
01:23:13,103 --> 01:23:16,140
- Hello, I'm here to ask you
if you remember this man.

1453
01:23:16,140 --> 01:23:17,420
- Excuse me.

1454
01:23:17,420 --> 01:23:18,830
Simpson.

1455
01:23:18,830 --> 01:23:21,553
Yeah, oh, no, no.

1456
01:23:22,560 --> 01:23:23,393
Look you better sit down, honey,

1457
01:23:23,393 --> 01:23:24,723
this is gonna take a while.

1458
01:23:25,965 --> 01:23:27,593
All right, come on give me the order.

1459
01:23:29,190 --> 01:23:33,223
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

1460
01:23:45,290 --> 01:23:47,223
- Hey, you blind?

1461
01:23:48,842 --> 01:23:50,060
- Huh?

1462
01:23:50,060 --> 01:23:51,053
- Read the sign.

1463
01:23:55,160 --> 01:23:57,080
If you're lookin' for work

1464
01:23:57,080 --> 01:23:59,843
you have to go to the end of the line.

1465
01:24:02,890 --> 01:24:06,043
To the end of the line.

1466
01:24:07,380 --> 01:24:09,530
- Yo, do I look like
I wanna work here bro?

1467
01:24:11,650 --> 01:24:15,140
- Oh, why don't you just get
the hell out of here then.

1468
01:24:15,140 --> 01:24:16,623
I said move it.

1469
01:24:27,641 --> 01:24:29,760
- Look, I'm tellin' ya for the last time

1470
01:24:29,760 --> 01:24:31,290
we got two men out sick today,

1471
01:24:31,290 --> 01:24:33,060
the line's down on number one.

1472
01:24:33,060 --> 01:24:34,300
No, no, I'll wait, I'll wait.

1473
01:24:34,300 --> 01:24:37,316
Look, you're on honey, you
better make it fast, huh.

1474
01:24:37,316 --> 01:24:38,210
- Do you recognize this man?

1475
01:24:38,210 --> 01:24:39,340
He used to work for you.

1476
01:24:39,340 --> 01:24:41,830
Arturo Montoya, Jose
Mendoza, or Reuben Reyes,

1477
01:24:41,830 --> 01:24:43,130
only his real name is Samuel Delacruz.

1478
01:24:43,130 --> 01:24:45,470
- Look, I had a lot of men work for me.

1479
01:24:45,470 --> 01:24:46,670
- All you have to sign this letter

1480
01:24:46,670 --> 01:24:47,630
that says he once worked for you

1481
01:24:47,630 --> 01:24:49,920
and he'll be able to
become a legal resident.

1482
01:24:49,920 --> 01:24:50,991
- That's it.

1483
01:24:50,991 --> 01:24:51,991
- That's it.

1484
01:24:53,640 --> 01:24:54,850
- Who are you?

1485
01:24:54,850 --> 01:24:56,400
- Marta Delacruz, his daughter.

1486
01:24:58,873 --> 01:25:02,373
(light suspenseful music)

1487
01:25:08,283 --> 01:25:09,950
- You look like him.

1488
01:25:17,463 --> 01:25:19,830
No, no, I'm here, look
you got me, I'm all ears.

1489
01:25:19,830 --> 01:25:22,480
You can drag me around
as much as you want.

1490
01:25:22,480 --> 01:25:25,910
Look, I promise you, I'll pack it myself,

1491
01:25:25,910 --> 01:25:29,410
I'll drive it across country if I have to.

1492
01:25:43,175 --> 01:25:44,627
- What's wrong?

1493
01:25:44,627 --> 01:25:45,720
- Can you believe that
creep actually thought

1494
01:25:45,720 --> 01:25:48,001
I wanted to work for these guys?

1495
01:25:48,001 --> 01:25:48,999
- [Marta] So.

1496
01:25:48,999 --> 01:25:52,233
- So, so I can do a lot
better than work here.

1497
01:25:54,360 --> 01:25:55,193
- I know.

1498
01:25:58,960 --> 01:26:00,100
- Did you get 'em signed?

1499
01:26:00,100 --> 01:26:02,460
- Yeah, but my hands are still sweaty.

1500
01:26:02,460 --> 01:26:03,303
- You got guts.

1501
01:26:04,630 --> 01:26:06,413
I mean you go past what scares you.

1502
01:26:08,570 --> 01:26:10,120
All right, so you're on a roll.

1503
01:26:10,980 --> 01:26:12,550
Where's the next one?

1504
01:26:12,550 --> 01:26:13,890
- It's late, I'm not really supposed

1505
01:26:13,890 --> 01:26:16,160
to be out at all, I'm grounded.

1506
01:26:16,160 --> 01:26:19,023
- Whatever it was you did it's worth it.

1507
01:26:21,573 --> 01:26:24,012
(car engine revving)

1508
01:26:24,012 --> 01:26:27,512
(light suspenseful music)

1509
01:26:42,021 --> 01:26:44,604
(upbeat music)

1510
01:29:16,023 --> 01:29:19,320
(cars thudding)

1511
01:29:19,320 --> 01:29:21,350
- I can believe he actually worked here.

1512
01:29:21,350 --> 01:29:24,150
- It makes my job look like
I'm a Wall Street executive.

1513
01:29:25,470 --> 01:29:28,769
Ah, your father's come a long way.

1514
01:29:28,769 --> 01:29:29,707
- Hey!

1515
01:29:29,707 --> 01:29:32,576
No kids messing around in here!

1516
01:29:32,576 --> 01:29:34,320
You break your necks I'm gonna get sued.

1517
01:29:34,320 --> 01:29:35,341
- Yo, chill out, all right.

1518
01:29:35,341 --> 01:29:36,951
We just wanna talk to the owner.

1519
01:29:36,951 --> 01:29:38,090
- Why?

1520
01:29:38,090 --> 01:29:39,940
- My father used to work for him,

1521
01:29:39,940 --> 01:29:41,790
all he has to do is sign this letter.

1522
01:29:45,570 --> 01:29:46,403
- Immigration.

1523
01:29:48,880 --> 01:29:50,913
No way, I can't hire illegals.

1524
01:29:52,125 --> 01:29:54,690
Hey, (speaks in foreign
language) over there,

1525
01:29:54,690 --> 01:29:55,523
(speaks in foreign language)!

1526
01:29:55,523 --> 01:29:57,040
- No, you don't understand.

1527
01:29:57,040 --> 01:29:58,417
All he has to do is say he worked here.

1528
01:29:58,417 --> 01:30:00,830
- How do I know he worked here.

1529
01:30:00,830 --> 01:30:03,940
I got hundreds of wetbacks
in and out of here.

1530
01:30:03,940 --> 01:30:05,230
- Because he sad.

1531
01:30:05,230 --> 01:30:07,350
- (laughs) He said.

1532
01:30:07,350 --> 01:30:08,763
He coulda said anything.

1533
01:30:09,940 --> 01:30:12,690
- Please, you're the last signature.

1534
01:30:12,690 --> 01:30:13,810
If you don't sign this letter

1535
01:30:13,810 --> 01:30:16,270
everything we've done will be for nothing.

1536
01:30:16,270 --> 01:30:18,770
- That's life, I ain't signing anything.

1537
01:30:18,770 --> 01:30:21,370
Now you kids get out of here!

1538
01:30:21,370 --> 01:30:22,280
What I'd say,

1539
01:30:22,280 --> 01:30:23,977
move that thing (speaking
in foreign language)!

1540
01:30:24,903 --> 01:30:27,170
- You know what Pops, you're
being a real jerk, man.

1541
01:30:27,170 --> 01:30:28,570
I mean everybody else
has signed the papers,

1542
01:30:28,570 --> 01:30:29,850
what's the problem?

1543
01:30:29,850 --> 01:30:32,130
- I ain't anybody else.

1544
01:30:32,130 --> 01:30:34,280
- I take it you like
be a slave owner, huh?

1545
01:30:36,520 --> 01:30:38,940
- You watch your step.

1546
01:30:38,940 --> 01:30:40,087
- Come on, let's get out of here.

1547
01:30:40,087 --> 01:30:41,970
- You know somethin' bro, you're lucky.

1548
01:30:41,970 --> 01:30:43,210
You're real lucky, man.

1549
01:30:43,210 --> 01:30:46,190
- Yeah, look at me, I'm trembling.

1550
01:30:46,190 --> 01:30:47,023
- Come on.

1551
01:30:51,400 --> 01:30:53,600
- That slime, he coulda
signed those papers.

1552
01:30:54,470 --> 01:30:56,460
Forget it, let's just go, all right.

1553
01:30:56,460 --> 01:30:57,380
What?

1554
01:30:57,380 --> 01:30:58,400
Marta, come back here.

1555
01:30:58,400 --> 01:30:59,640
What's a matter?

