01:30:59,640 --> 01:31:01,870
- Stay back, you two are
just gonna get in a fight.

1557
01:31:01,870 --> 01:31:03,159
- Don't you know that
you're giving into him,

1558
01:31:03,159 --> 01:31:04,347
that's what he wants you to do.

1559
01:31:04,347 --> 01:31:05,190
He want's you to crawl.

1560
01:31:05,190 --> 01:31:07,790
- I don't care what it
takes, I want that signature.

1561
01:31:15,660 --> 01:31:16,493
- What?

1562
01:31:18,100 --> 01:31:19,450
Oh, it's you.

1563
01:31:19,450 --> 01:31:22,200
Where's that little punk you were with?

1564
01:31:22,200 --> 01:31:25,240
- This man is my father,
he did work for you.

1565
01:31:25,240 --> 01:31:27,700
You may not remember
him, but it's the truth.

1566
01:31:27,700 --> 01:31:29,430
All you have to do is sign this letter.

1567
01:31:29,430 --> 01:31:30,290
You won't get in trouble

1568
01:31:30,290 --> 01:31:32,210
for something that happened years ago.

1569
01:31:32,210 --> 01:31:34,220
I know, I work at the amnesty office.

1570
01:31:34,220 --> 01:31:36,000
You can call and check if you want.

1571
01:31:36,000 --> 01:31:37,973
- I ain't callin' nobody.

1572
01:31:41,550 --> 01:31:45,170
- My father's worked so
hard, he deserves this.

1573
01:31:45,170 --> 01:31:49,368
To you it's just a signature
but it will changes he's life.

1574
01:31:49,368 --> 01:31:51,610
(inspirational music)

1575
01:31:51,610 --> 01:31:52,453
Please.

1576
01:31:54,690 --> 01:31:57,880
- You got a lotta guts coming back here.

1577
01:31:57,880 --> 01:31:58,800
Let me see that.

1578
01:32:07,573 --> 01:32:10,656
I don't know why I stick my neck out.

1579
01:32:15,448 --> 01:32:16,736
- Thank you.

1580
01:32:16,736 --> 01:32:18,743
You did a good thing.

1581
01:32:18,743 --> 01:32:19,993
- [Owner] Yeah.

1582
01:32:31,960 --> 01:32:33,043
- You did it?

1583
01:32:36,136 --> 01:32:37,398
You did it?

1584
01:32:37,398 --> 01:32:38,398
- We did it!

1585
01:32:39,613 --> 01:32:40,446
- Yeah.

1586
01:32:48,198 --> 01:32:49,698
Come on, let's go.

1587
01:33:06,632 --> 01:33:07,715
What's wrong?

1588
01:33:11,077 --> 01:33:13,540
- All of those horrible places we've been

1589
01:33:14,450 --> 01:33:18,530
and my father, I never had
any idea where he'd been,

1590
01:33:18,530 --> 01:33:19,913
what he'd done for us.

1591
01:33:21,510 --> 01:33:24,683
- He was just trying to keep
your, keep your life sweet.

1592
01:33:29,770 --> 01:33:30,620
What happens now?

1593
01:33:31,789 --> 01:33:33,039
- I don't know.

1594
01:33:33,903 --> 01:33:35,653
- Will I ever see you again?

1595
01:33:40,530 --> 01:33:43,863
(gentle romantic music)

1596
01:33:57,360 --> 01:33:58,220
- I gotta go.

1597
01:33:58,220 --> 01:33:59,533
- Wait, wait, wait.

1598
01:34:00,670 --> 01:34:02,880
I don't get it, today I'm your best friend

1599
01:34:04,170 --> 01:34:06,500
and then tomorrow I'm out of your life.

1600
01:34:06,500 --> 01:34:08,250
- No, it's just my father.

1601
01:34:08,250 --> 01:34:09,500
- What about your father?

1602
01:34:10,616 --> 01:34:13,380
I mean come on, I'm breaking
my back to help him.

1603
01:34:13,380 --> 01:34:14,690
- He doesn't know that.

1604
01:34:14,690 --> 01:34:15,890
- Yeah, but you know it.

1605
01:34:22,306 --> 01:34:24,980
You're not gonna tell him are you?

1606
01:34:24,980 --> 01:34:26,720
- I can't.

1607
01:34:26,720 --> 01:34:27,590
You don't understand.

1608
01:34:27,590 --> 01:34:28,778
- What is because I'm not good enough

1609
01:34:28,778 --> 01:34:30,661
for his little daughter,
is that what it is?

1610
01:34:30,661 --> 01:34:31,917
- No.

1611
01:34:31,917 --> 01:34:33,720
- You just went ahead and used me,

1612
01:34:33,720 --> 01:34:36,820
you got what you wanted, and
now it's goodbye Charlie.

1613
01:34:36,820 --> 01:34:38,120
- That's not fair.

1614
01:34:38,120 --> 01:34:39,220
- Well, you know what?

1615
01:34:40,150 --> 01:34:42,210
You go to on to your father, all right.

1616
01:34:42,210 --> 01:34:43,590
Go on to him, 'cause he's probably worried

1617
01:34:43,590 --> 01:34:45,240
about his little princess by now.

1618
01:34:49,010 --> 01:34:51,740
Oh, and another thing, next
time you need a chauffeur

1619
01:34:51,740 --> 01:34:53,640
look one up in the Yellow Pages, okay.

1620
01:35:00,336 --> 01:35:03,419
(car engine revving)

1621
01:35:16,500 --> 01:35:17,333
- Marta.

1622
01:35:20,030 --> 01:35:21,620
Where have you been?

1623
01:35:21,620 --> 01:35:22,700
- Papi.

1624
01:35:22,700 --> 01:35:25,701
- I have forbidden you to see that boy.

1625
01:35:25,701 --> 01:35:27,630
- It wasn't what you think.

1626
01:35:27,630 --> 01:35:29,470
- I don't know who you are anymore.

1627
01:35:29,470 --> 01:35:32,563
You're not my daughter, you
don't belong in this family!

1628
01:35:33,920 --> 01:35:36,610
- All my life I've looked up to you.

1629
01:35:36,610 --> 01:35:38,530
You taught me to believe in your dream

1630
01:35:38,530 --> 01:35:40,600
of who I am and who I could be,

1631
01:35:40,600 --> 01:35:43,973
and every time I try to be
those things you cut me down.

1632
01:35:45,080 --> 01:35:48,260
You're right, your daughter isn't here.

1633
01:35:48,260 --> 01:35:50,872
She finally grew up.

1634
01:35:50,872 --> 01:35:52,533
And if I don't belong in your family

1635
01:35:52,533 --> 01:35:55,360
it's because you won't make room for me.

1636
01:35:55,360 --> 01:35:56,960
You wanna know what I was doing.

1637
01:35:58,270 --> 01:36:00,413
This is what is what I
was doing with Ramon.

1638
01:36:03,844 --> 01:36:07,094
(light dramatic music)

1639
01:36:14,450 --> 01:36:17,080
- Everybody up, I'm
calling a family meeting.

1640
01:36:17,080 --> 01:36:18,319
Your father has something to tell you

1641
01:36:18,319 --> 01:36:19,869
and I'm only gonna say it once.

1642
01:36:22,820 --> 01:36:27,603
Children, your father has
always asked you for two things,

1643
01:36:28,680 --> 01:36:32,973
never to lie and never to lose your dream.

1644
01:36:35,560 --> 01:36:39,983
I wanted to be an American,
that was my dream, but I lied.

1645
01:36:42,810 --> 01:36:46,593
In fact, I am not a
citizen of this country.

1646
01:36:49,270 --> 01:36:53,413
That lie had a reason,
I wanted to protect you.

1647
01:36:55,523 --> 01:36:56,923
And I'm not ashamed of that.

1648
01:36:58,210 --> 01:37:01,823
But somebody in this
family wanted to help,

1649
01:37:03,129 --> 01:37:05,567
and because of my pride I refused.

1650
01:37:09,090 --> 01:37:10,740
Marta wanted me to keep my dream,

1651
01:37:13,965 --> 01:37:14,915
and I shut her out.

1652
01:37:17,660 --> 01:37:22,660
Amnesty is forgiveness, I
hope Marta can forgive me.

1653
01:37:32,776 --> 01:37:35,776
(children giggling)

1654
01:37:45,930 --> 01:37:48,780
- You're everything I
ever hoped you would be.

1655
01:37:48,780 --> 01:37:51,493
You deserve this day,
you've earned it, mija.

1656
01:38:01,880 --> 01:38:05,023
- Mommy, you made this.

1657
01:38:05,023 --> 01:38:06,544
- Mm-hmm.

1658
01:38:06,544 --> 01:38:07,544
- Thank you.

1659
01:38:08,890 --> 01:38:12,705
- Hurry up, girls, they don't
wait for nobody at the church.

1660
01:38:12,705 --> 01:38:15,955
(church bells ringing)

1661
01:38:17,560 --> 01:38:20,100
- Marta Alecia Delacruz,

1662
01:38:20,100 --> 01:38:22,897
this is your 15th birthday
(speaks in foreign language).

1663
01:38:26,200 --> 01:38:29,223
It marks your passage from
childhood into the grownup world.

1664
01:38:30,520 --> 01:38:32,170
As you cross this threshold

1665
01:38:33,270 --> 01:38:36,010
remember you have the power within you

1666
01:38:36,010 --> 01:38:38,133
to find everything you're searching for.

1667
01:38:39,720 --> 01:38:40,973
Never doubt yourself.

1668
01:38:42,763 --> 01:38:44,090
And if others doubt you

1669
01:38:45,160 --> 01:38:47,260
remember God wants you to become complete.

1670
01:38:48,690 --> 01:38:52,493
May he look upon you with
kindness and give you peace.

1671
01:38:58,003 --> 01:38:59,155
- Adios, Manuel.

1672
01:38:59,155 --> 01:39:01,226
- Thank you.
- Gracias, Tina.

1673
01:39:01,226 --> 01:39:02,059
- Thank you.
- Adios.

1674
01:39:02,059 --> 01:39:03,563
- This is a proud day for both of you.

1675
01:39:04,498 --> 01:39:05,331
- Yeah.

1676
01:39:06,730 --> 01:39:11,130
- Congratulations, those
are your temporary papers.

1677
01:39:11,130 --> 01:39:13,730
You can use them until your
permanent card comes in.

1678
01:39:18,400 --> 01:39:19,233
- Thank you.

1679
01:39:19,233 --> 01:39:20,547
- You have quite a daughter.

1680
01:39:21,953 --> 01:39:26,370
(Guest speaking in foreign language)

1681
01:39:31,465 --> 01:39:34,174
(gentle music)

1682
01:39:34,174 --> 01:39:38,507
- Marta, just yesterday I,
I carried you right here.

1683
01:39:42,100 --> 01:39:45,283
Today, I set you free.

1684
01:39:46,811 --> 01:39:47,644
- Papi.

1685
01:39:50,510 --> 01:39:51,343
- Marta.

1686
01:39:52,883 --> 01:39:54,240
I've just been told that someone

1687
01:39:54,240 --> 01:39:56,420
has tampered with the files.
- What?

1688
01:39:56,420 --> 01:39:59,125
- There is some officials
waiting inside the office

1689
01:39:59,125 --> 01:40:00,513
that would like to speak with you.

1690
01:40:16,136 --> 01:40:18,105
- [Group] Surprise!

1691
01:40:18,105 --> 01:40:21,438
(upbeat mariachi music)

1692
01:40:38,054 --> 01:40:39,519
(singing in foreign language)

1693
01:40:39,519 --> 01:40:42,186
- Amigos, the clothes, the food,

1694
01:40:43,033 --> 01:40:45,910
(speaks in foreign language),
were all made by you.

1695
01:40:45,910 --> 01:40:48,623
You are our family, you
are where we come from,

1696
01:40:49,467 --> 01:40:50,640
and where we belong.

1697
01:40:50,640 --> 01:40:53,467
- Thank you, everybody from
the bottom of our hearts.

1698
01:40:59,421 --> 01:41:02,171
(girls cheering)

1699
01:41:03,189 --> 01:41:04,359
- So beautiful.

1700
01:41:04,359 --> 01:41:05,491
These are from Gabby's quince.

1701
01:41:05,491 --> 01:41:06,680
- I borrowed them back.

1702
01:41:06,680 --> 01:41:08,771
- Ay, you've seen one
dress you've seen 'em all.

1703
01:41:08,771 --> 01:41:09,746
(girls cheering)

1704
01:41:09,746 --> 01:41:12,926
(singing in foreign language)

1705
01:41:12,926 --> 01:41:15,676
(group cheering)

1706
01:41:28,906 --> 01:41:29,739
- Marta.

1707
01:41:29,739 --> 01:41:30,913
- [Group] To Marta.

1708
01:41:30,913 --> 01:41:33,124
To Marta, to Marta.

1709
01:41:33,124 --> 01:41:34,041
- To Marta.

1710
01:41:37,461 --> 01:41:40,794
(gentle romantic music)

1711
01:41:42,163 --> 01:41:43,431
Congratulations.

1712
01:41:43,431 --> 01:41:44,630
- He let you come.

1713
01:41:44,630 --> 01:41:45,977
- Hey, he asked me to come.

1714
01:41:45,977 --> 01:41:49,210
And I tell you what, I wouldn't
miss this for anything.

1715
01:41:49,210 --> 01:41:50,043
Come here.

1716
01:41:56,440 --> 01:41:58,883
Sit down, and watch.

1717
01:42:17,841 --> 01:42:20,341
(Ramon sighs)

1718
01:42:37,570 --> 01:42:38,403
- Thank you.

1719
